<div id="review_3001929130" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3001929130" />
    <a title="Tania" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6450088-tania"><img alt="Tania" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603638299p2/6450088.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3001929130?book_show_action=true">Dec 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tania" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tania" href="/user/show/6450088-tania">Tania</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=best">best</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=favorite-books">favorite-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3001929130" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9343649122602261374"><blockquote>&quot;Always more, always hungrily scratching for more.&quot;</blockquote><br/>I started reading this just before I had to switch off the light, but had to finish this raw, heartbreaking novel in one sitting - luckily for me it comes in at under 150 pages.<br/> <br/>I was hooked by the poetic yet urgent quality of the writing from page one, and I thought the we/us POV of the three brothers in many parts of the book was unique and powerful. <br/><br/>What I loved most about this book (except for the exquisite writing) is that the author portra</span>
  <span id="freeText9343649122602261374" style="display:none"><blockquote>"Always more, always hungrily scratching for more."</blockquote><br />I started reading this just before I had to switch off the light, but had to finish this raw, heartbreaking novel in one sitting - luckily for me it comes in at under 150 pages.<br /> <br />I was hooked by the poetic yet urgent quality of the writing from page one, and I thought the we/us POV of the three brothers in many parts of the book was unique and powerful. <br /><br />What I loved most about this book (except for the exquisite writing) is that the author portrays the family situation exactly as a young child would experience and react to it. There is also no judgement made on anyone, as everyone is doing the best they can in a bad situation.<br /><br />My only issue with this book is that the ending felt accelerated and in some sense disconnected from the rest of the story, but other than that I thought this novel was flawless. Highly recommended.<br /><br /><blockquote>"We hit and we kept on hitting; we were allowed to be what we were, frightened and vengeful - little animals, clawing at what we needed."</blockquote></span>
