        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer216027974" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13079487212333073370">By far the best book of 2011. Not sure what to say about those reviewers who believe this book has no literary merit or that Torres is a bad writer. The book is brilliant - yes, it is short. Yes, it is sparse. No, it is not a linear plot, being episodic. But it cuts deeply - if you can set yourself aside for a moment and really sink into the story, imagine what life was like for this family, for this young boy - so different from anyone else he knew.. it seems impossible not to &apos;get it.&apos; Unfortu</span>
  <span id="freeText13079487212333073370" style="display:none">By far the best book of 2011. Not sure what to say about those reviewers who believe this book has no literary merit or that Torres is a bad writer. The book is brilliant - yes, it is short. Yes, it is sparse. No, it is not a linear plot, being episodic. But it cuts deeply - if you can set yourself aside for a moment and really sink into the story, imagine what life was like for this family, for this young boy - so different from anyone else he knew.. it seems impossible not to 'get it.' Unfortunately, there are those out there who just don't get it - and I think the negative reviews come from a certain lack of understanding or empathy, period. <br /><br /><br />Read the review at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.roofbeamreader.com">www.roofbeamreader.com</a></span>
