<span id="freeTextContainer7178642432663908762">Very impressed by Justin Torres. In 125 pages, he presents a complete, subtle, short, brutal, beautiful transformation from the family unit of childhood to the scarred and loved individual that emerges. Given that it&apos;s so brief, I don&apos;t want to say too much. The chapters are capable of literally shocking memories out of you -- each is a little visceral tale that wholly hones in on those feelings from youth (a comfortable afternoon with Mom, familial respect-both deserved and forced, sibling prot</span>
  <span id="freeText7178642432663908762" style="display:none">Very impressed by Justin Torres. In 125 pages, he presents a complete, subtle, short, brutal, beautiful transformation from the family unit of childhood to the scarred and loved individual that emerges. Given that it's so brief, I don't want to say too much. The chapters are capable of literally shocking memories out of you -- each is a little visceral tale that wholly hones in on those feelings from youth (a comfortable afternoon with Mom, familial respect-both deserved and forced, sibling protection, etc.). Ultimately hits hard...losing something by being the uncommon element in your tribe, diverging from the expected, growing up.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7178642432663908762" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

